People will argue for ages as to what type of bonds you should have. BND/BNDW and Bond (funds) with maturity dates aligned with your time horizon are good choices to start with&#160;&#x21a9;&#xfe0e;
The percentage of take-home or after tax income that you don&rsquo;t spend in a given year&#160;&#x21a9;&#xfe0e;
